1
00:00:01,790 --> 00:00:05,083
<i>Kids, in the spring of 2011,
Zoey and I broke up.</i>

2
00:00:05,208 --> 00:00:06,380
<i>But the good news...</i>

3
00:00:06,546 --> 00:00:09,493
<i>Goliath National Bank was finally ready
to demolish The Arcadian</i>

4
00:00:09,618 --> 00:00:12,066
<i>and build the new headquarters
I'd designed for them.</i>

5
00:00:14,117 --> 00:00:16,261
<i>The only problem was
I kept butting heads</i>

6
00:00:16,386 --> 00:00:19,310
<i>with my project supervisor
on one very important issue.</i>

7
00:00:19,435 --> 00:00:21,437
I want to press the button
to blow up The Arcadian!

8
00:00:21,603 --> 00:00:23,147
- I want to press it!
- No, I want!

9
00:00:23,313 --> 00:00:24,693
I want to press it!

10
00:00:24,818 --> 00:00:27,639
I dated you both and neither of you
is good at pressing

11
00:00:27,764 --> 00:00:29,612
or even finding the button.

12
00:00:29,778 --> 00:00:31,773
After some awkward pawing around,
that building

13
00:00:31,898 --> 00:00:34,487
is going to fake an implosion,
say, "Baby, that was great",

14
00:00:34,612 --> 00:00:35,743
and go to sleep.

15
00:00:36,943 --> 00:00:38,412
She means you.

16
00:00:39,162 --> 00:00:40,479
I want to press it.

17
00:00:40,604 --> 00:00:41,916
I'm gonna press it!

18
00:00:42,082 --> 00:00:43,522
It's just a button, okay?

19
00:00:43,647 --> 00:00:45,905
Can we just talk
about something else, please?

20
00:00:47,251 --> 00:00:49,340
I ran into Zoey yesterday.

21
00:00:50,735 --> 00:00:52,701
That's the first time
since the breakup.

22
00:00:52,826 --> 00:00:53,886
How's she doing?

23
00:00:54,474 --> 00:00:57,598
I'm still unemployed,
so I had to get a couple roommates.

24
00:00:58,217 --> 00:00:59,367
Saving money.

25
00:00:59,665 --> 00:01:01,731
Making new friends.
No downside.

26
00:01:01,856 --> 00:01:03,771
They're all 22 and sell drugs.

27
00:01:04,108 --> 00:01:05,816
Which means they're not taking them.

28
00:01:05,941 --> 00:01:08,088
So, that's a win.

29
00:01:10,193 --> 00:01:12,655
I can tell you're really busy
so I should...

30
00:01:12,821 --> 00:01:14,121
I'll let you go.

31
00:01:15,657 --> 00:01:17,405
You want to get coffee sometime?

32
00:01:17,784 --> 00:01:20,121
You know "coffee" is code
for "I want to get back together"?

33
00:01:20,287 --> 00:01:23,874
At first I wasn't sure, but then,
she said something that got me thinking.

34
00:01:24,291 --> 00:01:26,161
I want to get back together.

35
00:01:26,585 --> 00:01:27,909
Don't worry, we're not.

36
00:01:28,034 --> 00:01:30,589
I just, I feel bad Zoey's
having such a hard time.

37
00:01:31,507 --> 00:01:34,552
You know what might
make you feel better, buddy?

38
00:01:34,718 --> 00:01:37,138
- I'm not letting you press the button.
- I want to press it!

39
00:01:38,085 --> 00:01:40,391
<i>Sadly, that's all you need
to know about my summer.</i>

40
00:01:40,958 --> 00:01:44,395
<i>Around this time, Uncle Marshall was
still having a tough time finding a job.</i>

41
00:01:44,520 --> 00:01:46,814
He's out printing out a whole
new batch of résumés

42
00:01:46,980 --> 00:01:49,483
because he misspelled the phrase
"detail-oriented."

43
00:01:49,971 --> 00:01:51,507
And when he gets back home,

44
00:01:51,632 --> 00:01:54,196
he is going to find his favorite soup
there waiting for him.

45
00:01:54,362 --> 00:01:55,708
That's sweet, Lily,

46
00:01:55,833 --> 00:01:58,284
but didn't you guys get
food poisoning here one time?

47
00:01:59,484 --> 00:02:00,489
Three times.

48
00:02:00,614 --> 00:02:02,318
But they're really nice about it.

49
00:02:02,443 --> 00:02:05,791
Their policy is,
"Get sick, get a free gallon of soup".

50
00:02:10,599 --> 00:02:14,341
<i>And so, Lily dropped off Marshall's
surprise soup and headed back to work</i>

51
