dary adjacent.

69
00:03:54,603 --> 00:03:56,753
Legendary adjacent!

70
00:03:57,678 --> 00:03:58,679
You okay?

71
00:04:01,907 --> 00:04:03,784
This morning I was talking
to the foreman.

72
00:04:04,566 --> 00:04:05,716
Hey, hotshot.

73
00:04:06,286 --> 00:04:08,831
You know, Rod,
I'm loving that nickname,

74
00:04:09,180 --> 00:04:11,500
and I can tell
it's totally affectionate,

75
00:04:12,625 --> 00:04:13,961
but I'd prefer Ted.

76
00:04:14,306 --> 00:04:17,035
Yeah, but you're such a hotshot,

77
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:19,174
I figured I'd just call you hotshot.

78
00:04:20,175 --> 00:04:21,208
Pick one.

79
00:04:21,333 --> 00:04:22,841
And make sure you like it.

80
00:04:22,966 --> 00:04:24,729
There's going to be 50,000 of these

81
00:04:24,854 --> 00:04:27,725
in your big, hotshot building,
hotshot.

82
00:04:28,447 --> 00:04:31,145
50,000 lightbulbs!

83
00:04:31,311 --> 00:04:32,730
What if this one's too bright?

84
00:04:32,896 --> 00:04:36,113
What if this one flickers
and gives everyone a weird headache?

85
00:04:36,238 --> 00:04:39,862
Do you know how many people
it takes to change 50,000 lightbulbs?

86
00:04:40,028 --> 00:04:43,073
Are these people Irish, Polish, blondes?
What are we dealing with here?

87
00:04:43,520 --> 00:04:45,337
There's so many decisions to be made.

88
00:04:45,462 --> 00:04:48,204
What if I make all the wrong ones
and my building just sucks?

89
00:04:48,370 --> 00:04:50,424
Not possible.
Your building is new.

90
00:04:50,549 --> 00:04:51,877
And I have one rule.

91
00:04:52,002 --> 00:04:54,627
New is always better.

92
00:04:54,793 --> 00:04:57,338
You can't keep saying you have one rule
if they're always different.

93
00:04:57,903 --> 00:05:00,612
But "new is always better"
is my oldest rule,

94
00:05:00,737 --> 00:05:02,134
which makes it the best.

95
00:05:06,387 --> 00:05:07,514
Everything okay?

96
00:05:07,985 --> 00:05:10,267
Lily got food poisoning
from some soup.

97
00:05:11,434 --> 00:05:13,896
And then I ate the soup,
exactly three hours later.

98
00:05:14,021 --> 00:05:18,196
Which means I can see exactly
three hours into my future,

99
00:05:20,086 --> 00:05:21,352
and it doesn't...

100
00:05:21,477 --> 00:05:22,478
look...

101
00:05:23,121 --> 00:05:24,122
good.

102
00:05:24,739 --> 00:05:26,391
<i>I tried to be supportive.</i>

103
00:05:26,516 --> 00:05:29,016
Oh, baby,
can you just hold me, please?

104
00:05:30,226 --> 00:05:31,533
Of course, baby.

105
00:05:35,542 --> 00:05:37,015
<i>But when Lily gets going</i>

106
00:05:37,140 --> 00:05:39,713
<i>she sounds like a velociraptor
from Jurassic Park.</i>

107
00:05:44,545 --> 00:05:46,324
<i>But then I realized...</i>

108
00:05:46,449 --> 00:05:48,760
<i>a man can do a lot of living
in three hours.</i>

109
00:05:49,846 --> 00:05:54,728
So, I'm out experiencing this beautiful,
crazy dance called life.

110
00:05:56,062 --> 00:05:59,233
My last meal.
MacClaren's famous jalapeño poppers.

111
00:05:59,709 --> 00:06:01,478
My doctor says
I need to eat healthier,

112
00:06:01,603 --> 00:06:04,291
so I figured the round-trip flight
these babies are about to take

113
00:06:04,416 --> 00:06:06,865
will land them permanently
on the no-fry list.

114
00:06:08,431 --> 00:06:09,738
Good-bye, my friend.

115
00:06:12,009 --> 00:06:13,597
It's been a hell of a ride.

116
00:06:16,708 --> 00:06:17,808
I have to...

117
00:06:20,732 --> 00:06:21,733
Hey, babe.

118
00:06:22,743 --> 00:06:24,623
The gang says feel better.

119
00:06:24,748 --> 00:06:25,573
Thanks.

120
00:06:25,698 --> 00:06:26,510
Wait!

121
00:06:26,676 --> 00:06:29,513
You didn't tell them
I had food poisoning, did you?

122
00:06:31,306 --> 00:06:34,874
Marshall, when it's stomach stuff,
you just say "under the weather",

123
00:06:34,999 --> 00:06:37,896
or people start picturing you
doing unspeakable things.

124
00:06:38,062 --> 00:06:38,970
I know.

125
00:06:39,095 --> 00:06:41,734
I just said
that you had the sniffles.

126
00:06:42,181 --> 00:06:44,081
No one is picturing anything

127
00:06:44,206 --> 00:06:46,113
but little red-nosed you

128
00:06:46,279 --> 00:06:48,449
under a blankie with some hot tea.

129
00:06:48,615 --> 00:06:51,285
I wonder what end
it's coming out of Lily right now.

130
00:06:51,835 --> 00:06:53,203
I bet it's her tushie.

131
00:06:53,570 --> 00:06:54,870
I bet it's both.

132
00:07:00,222 --> 00:07:01,684
Speaking of explosions...

133
00:07:01,809 --> 00:07:04,131
Enough already, Ted!
That button's mine!

134
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:05,758
Yeah, fine, okay.

135
00:07:05,924 --> 00:07:08,385
I got you this job, so I...
Say what?

136
00:07:08,551 --> 00:07:09,678
Whatever.

137
00:07:10,149 --> 00:07:11,167
It's yours.

138
00:07:11,292 --> 00:07:12,392
I gotta run.

139
00:07:19,814 --> 00:07:20,606
Yes.

140
00:07:21,793 --> 00:07:24,568
It's Bloom, Greenberg and Associates.
They want me to come interview.

141
00:07:27,210 --> 00:07:28,756
I know it's risky to go,

142
00:07:28,881 --> 00:07:31,742
but this is the best environmental
law firm in New York, my dream job.

143
00:07:34,056 --> 00:07:36,206
Great idea, babe.
I'll ask them.

144
00:07:37,794 --> 00:07:40,584
Is it at all possible,
could I come in on Monday?

145
00:07:42,398 --> 00:07:44,826
Okay, I'll, I'll see you at 5:00.
Thank you.

146
00:07:49,850 --> 00:07:52,329
I love and believe in you too, baby.

147
00:07:53,934 --> 00:07:54,890
Why would Ted

148
00:07:55,056 --> 00:07:56,683
just give up the button like that?

149
00:07:58,184 --> 00:07:59,325
He forgot his phone.

150
00:08:01,519 --> 00:08:02,815
"See you in an hour."

151
00:08:02,981 --> 00:08:04,790
- Who's that from?
- Zoey.

152
00:08:05,264 --> 00:08:06,622
They're meeting for coffee.

153
00:08:08,184 --> 00:08:09,892
Ted's getting back together with her!

154
00:08:15,082 --> 00:08:17,829
Why would Ted get back together
with Zoey? He's doing great.

155
00:08:17,995 --> 00:08:19,997
After a breakup,
we all think we're doing great.

156
00:08:20,590 --> 00:08:23,157
Sometimes the tiniest trigger
can unravel you

157
00:08:23,282 --> 00:08:24,844
and send you crawling right back.

158
00:08:25,419 --> 00:08:28,548
Ted isn't getting back with Zoey
because of lightbulbs.

159
00:08:28,714 --> 00:08:30,341
Ted's gone back for less.

160
00:08:34,636 --> 00:08:36,001
Hi, Natalie.

161
00:08:36,385 --> 00:08:38,150
You want to get coffee sometime?

162
00:08:38,275 --> 00:08:39,808
CARTON

163
00:08:42,433 --> 00:08:43,229
Bro.

164
00:08:44,237 --> 00:08:45,940
Ted, I only have one rule.

165
00:08:46,106 --> 00:08:48,734
But I can't reach the worst part.

166
00:08:49,943 --> 00:08:51,166
Hi, Karen.

167
00:08:51,548 --> 00:08:52,937
Want to get coffee sometime?

168
00:08:53,062 --> 00:08:54,729
CARTON

169
00:08:55,286 --> 00:08:57,172
<i>Coming up next, our two local pandas,</i>

170
00:08:57,297 --> 00:08:59,866
<i>Ming Ming and Bao Bao,
are expecting a baby.</i>

171
00:09:01,371 --> 00:09:03,195
You want to get coffee sometime...?

172
00:09:03,485 --> 00:09:04,767
Get it together, bro.

173
00:09:06,133 --> 00:09:08,617
According to my calculations,
at 6:00 PM,

174
00:09:09,323 --> 00:09:10,946
my body is gonna pay out

175
00:09:11,071 --> 00:09:13,453
like the most disgusting
slot machine in the world.

176
00:09:14,068 --> 00:09:15,916
That gives me two hours
to go do the interview

177
00:09:16,041 --> 00:09:17,346
and still get back in time.

178
00:09:17,856 --> 00:09:19,807
What if you hit the jackpot early?

179
00:09:20,469 --> 00:09:21,697
Don't worry.

180
00:09:22,487 --> 00:09:23,837
I'll be prepared.

181
00:09:41,161 --> 00:09:43,271
I'm talking your ear off, sorry.

182
00:09:43,396 --> 00:09:45,625
Is there anything
I can do for you, sweetie?

183
00:09:47,673 --> 00:09:50,418
Can... I... borrow...

184
00:09:51,812 --> 00:09:53,382
an adult diaper?

185
00:09:56,093 --> 00:09:57,553
Let's stop Ted.
Where are they meeting?

186
00:09:57,909 --> 00:10:00,833
Zoey wrote, "Meet me
at 6:00, where it all began,

187
00:10:00,958 --> 00:10:03,100
where you gave me the orchid
at the intersection."

188
00:10:03,266 --> 00:10:05,290
That's good.
All we have to do is think back

189
00:10:05,415 --> 00:10:07,521
to the time Ted told us
about his first date with Zoey.

190
00:10:07,993 --> 00:10:09,825
Amazing first date with Zoey!

191
00:10:09,950 --> 00:10:11,237
We met at the intersection.

192
00:10:14,541 --> 00:10:16,572
That's sweet.

193
00:10:17,140 --> 00:10:18,491
You weren't listening either?

194
00:10:18,657 --> 00:10:19,788
I was in a coma.

195
00:10:19,913 --> 00:10:22,495
I mean, who pays attention
to that sappy romantic crap?

196
00:10:24,696 --> 00:10:26,874
Yeah, I wasn't listening, either.

197
00:10:27,040 --> 00:10:29,544
Ted really can go on about a bitch.

198
00:10:30,038 --> 00:10:30,984
Great.

199
00:10:31,109 --> 00:10:33,381
He could be anywhere.
We're flat out of clues.

200
00:10:33,547 --> 00:10:35,154
Wait. Ted left a message.

201
00:10:35,279 --> 00:10:37,506
I could hear it
'cause I was in the bathroom...

202
00:10:37,930 --> 00:10:39,554
blowing my nose.
I have the sniffles.

203
00:10:41,962 --> 00:10:43,544
<i>Hey, Lily,
hope you're feeling better.</i>

204
00:10:43,669 --> 00:10:46,394
<i>Marshall told us you're exploding from
both ends like a busted fire hydrant.</i>

205
00:10:47,602 --> 00:10:48,666
Damn it.

206
00:10:48,919 --> 00:10:52,375
<i>Anyway, listen, I was going
to get back together with Zoey today,</i>

207
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:54,652
<i>but I came to my senses
on the way out here, so...</i>

208
00:10:54,818 --> 00:10:56,028
<i>False alarm.</i>

209
00:10:57,295 --> 00:10:58,364
<i>Oh, crap.</i>

210
00:10:58,844 --> 00:11:00,229
<i>Just stepped in some gum.</i>

211
00:11:00,828 --> 00:11:02,618
<i>I'm getting back together with Zoey!</i>

212
00:11:03,290 --> 00:11:04,704
We're never gonna find him.

213
00:11:04,870 --> 00:11:05,871
Wait.

214
00:11:05,996 --> 00:11:08,624
That's was a subway announcement
in the background.

215
00:11:08,790 --> 00:11:09,875
I speak conductor.

216
00:11:10,041 --> 00:11:11,335


217
00:11:12,724 --> 00:11:14,088
Got it.
Ted's at...

218
00:11:24,097 --> 00:11:27,059
- Ted's at Smith and Ninth Street.
- That's the intersection.

219
00:11:27,225 --> 00:11:29,603
That's in Brooklyn. How are we
ever gonna get there in time?

220
00:11:29,769 --> 00:11:30,980
Way ahead of ya.

221
00:11:38,869 --> 00:11:40,584
Jake Bloom. Great to meet you.

222
00:11:41,281 --> 00:11:43,284
I'm sorry about the stench.

223
00:11:43,450 --> 00:11:45,507
We're suing a factory
that's been dumping raw sewage

224
00:11:45,632 --> 00:11:46,704
into a marshland.

225
00:11:47,143 --> 00:11:48,289
Ten minutes ago,

226
00:11:48,642 --> 00:11:51,584
I was knee-deep
in liquefied human feces.

227
00:11:52,232 --> 00:11:54,189
And that was just on the F train.

228
00:11:57,018 --> 00:11:59,119
I can't believe Ted's getting
back together with Zoey.

229
00:11:59,244 --> 00:12:02,136
- They're a total train wreck.
- Unmitigated disaster.

230
00:12:02,302 --> 00:12:03,684
Worst couple ever.

231
00:12:05,346 --> 00:12:06,698
Yeah, almost as bad as us.

232
00:12:08,669 --> 00:12:09,782
We were a mess.

233
00:12:10,430 --> 00:12:12,646
Do you remember how awful
I looked by the end?

234
00:12:12,812 --> 00:12:14,649
My hair was falling out,

235
00:12:14,774 --> 00:12:17,193
my skin was gray,
my back was hunched.

236
00:12:17,359 --> 00:12:19,726
What about me?
I got so fat,

237
00:12:19,851 --> 00:12:22,198
at the end of a date,
you'd unhook my bra.

238
00:12:23,041 --> 00:12:25,493
You were the only boyfriend
I ever motorboated.

239
00:12:27,839 --> 00:12:31,080
Thank God we're not sentimental saps
who panic and get back together.

240
00:12:31,205 --> 00:12:32,166
Seriously,

241
00:12:32,459 --> 00:12:34,001
why would people do that?

242
00:12:36,717 --> 00:12:38,067
I guess I get it.

243
00:12:38,630 --> 00:12:39,715
What do you mean?

244
00:12:39,881 --> 00:12:42,231
Well, no matter how bad things got...

245
00:12:44,932 --> 00:12:47,481
Ted really did love Zoey
for a minute there.

246
00:12:48,171 --> 00:12:49,172
Didn't he?

247
00:12:55,617 --> 00:12:56,440
He did.

248
00:13:00,366 --> 00:13:01,816
She loved him, too.

249
00:13:03,507 --> 00:13:04,532
Didn't she?

250
00:13:06,425 --> 00:13:07,495
Yeah, she did.

251
00:13:14,124 --> 00:13:16,460
Smith and Ninth Street.

